ent and Reporting**\n- Enter and update data in relevant systems and spreadsheets.\n- Generate and analyze reports to support business decisions.\n- Maintain accurate and up-to-date records of client interactions and transactions.\n\n5. **Client and Team Communication**\n- Serve as the point of contact for clients during the transaction process.\n- Provide regular updates to clients and agents on the status of transactions.\n- Coordinate with team members to ensure alignment and efficient workflow.\n\n6. **Marketing Support**\n- Assist with the creation and distribution of marketing materials and campaigns.\n- Manage social media accounts and online presence.\n- Support the planning and execution of open houses and other events.\n\n7. **Technology and Tools**\n- Stay updated with the latest features and updates in EXP Realty software.\n- Troubleshoot and resolve any technical issues related to the software tools.\n- Provide training and support to team members on the use of these tools.\n #### Skills for a social media strategist (luxury) \n\n1. **Social Media Strategy and Management**\n- Expertise in creating and executing social media strategies.\n- Experience in brand building and enhancing online presence.\n- Familiarity with real estate industry trends and social media best practices.\n\n2. **Content Creation**\n- Proficiency in graphic design tools such as Canva and video editing software like CapCut.\n- Ability to create lifestyle reels, educational reels, and real estate carousels.\n- Strong skills in video editing and creating engaging visual content.\n\n3. **Brand Building**\n- Ability to develop and maintain a consistent brand voice and aesthetic.\n- Experience in growing a brand’s presence on social media.\n- Understanding of how to position a brand in the real estate market.\n\n4. **Trend Acclimation**\n- Ability to identify and leverage current trends in the real estate industry.\n- Experience in creating trendy and relevant content that resonates with